caption:
This photograph features a close-up view of a large, dark-colored frog peering directly into the camera. The frog's skin has a shiny, textured appearance, possibly damp, and radiates an iridescent blue-black color. Its eyes are striking and prominent with horizontal, almond-shaped pupils surrounded by a delicate green hue. The frog is partly submerged in water, as indicated by shimmering water textures around its face and body. 

In the foreground, there are a few green leaves dappling over the water surface, suggesting the frog might be in a natural, leafy water body, perhaps a pond. The lighting is soft, highlighting the glistening details of the frog's skin and creating a slight reflection in the eyes. The overall mood is calm and focused, capturing the quiet ambiance of the frog's natural habitat.
title: Close-up of a bullfrog (Rana catesbiana Shaw) sitting on the edge of Tin Mine Lake, Washington. Near Seattle, Washington. From the Environmental Protection Agency's Project DOCUMERICA collection, "In Praise of Forests". ENTHEOS. Summer, 1974.
